#### Import changes for modified files

|Files|Import difference|
|-|-|

</details>

---

<details><summary>

#### Declarations diff

</summary>

`+ instance (n : ℕ) : OfNat NONote n`
`+ instance (n : ℕ) : OfNat ONote n`
`+ instance : NatCast NONote`
`+ instance : NatCast ONote`
`+ instance : One NONote`
`+ natCast_one`
`+ natCast_succ`
`+ natCast_zero`
`+ nfBelow_natCast`
`+ nf_natCast`
`++ natCast_ofNat`
`++ repr_natCast`
`++ repr_zero`
`+-+- ofNat`
`- nat`
`- nf_ofNat`
`-++ repr_ofNat`
`-++ repr_one`
<details>
  <summary>You can run this locally as follows</summary>


```bash
## summary with just the declaration names:
./scripts/declarations_diff.sh <optional_commit>

## more verbose report:
./scripts/declarations_diff.sh long <optional_commit>
```
</details>

The doc-module for `script/declarations_diff.sh` contains some details about this script.

</details>
I'd argue this style is better

```suggestion
instance : NatCast ONote where
  natCast
  | 0 => 0
  | Nat.succ n => oadd 0 n.succPNat 0
```
I thought this was superceded by the `NatCast` instance but I've since learned that's not the case. Will revert.

For these instances you should at least have a lemma `natCast_ofNat : natCast (noindex (OfNat.ofNat n)) = OfNat.ofNat n`

(assuming you don't get this for free with a later `AddCommMonoidWithOne` instance).
(it also doesn't mention a cast; did you mean for one side to be ascribed as `Ordinal`?
I was trying to add the natCast_ofNat theorem you described earlier, what did I do wrong?
What type do you intend the RHS to be?

Maybe you meant
```suggestion
    ↑(no_index (OfNat.ofNat n) : ℕ) = (OfNat.ofNat n : ONote) :=
```

pullRequest.title: chore(SetTheory/Ordinal/Notation): use `NatCast`
